mouserial (3.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Version 3.1.0 - Feature enhancements and bug fixes
  - UART waveform visualization (click log entries to view signal waveform)
  - Real-time waveform display toggle
  - 5 built-in themes (Dark, Light, Solarized, Monokai, High Contrast)
  - Configurable log cache limit (1000~100000 entries)
  - Encoding auto-detection (UTF-8/GBK heuristic)
  - HEX+text dual view in HEX display mode
  - Linux dialout group permission detection with guided fix
  - socat dependency auto-check with distro-specific install commands
  - Window geometry and layout persistence across sessions
  - Settings panel collapse/expand support
  - Font scale range extended to 0.8~2.0
  - Modbus function codes expanded (8 codes including multi-register write)
  - Log export enhanced with HEX format and metadata header
  - PyQt5/PyQt6 compatibility for data_panel.py
  - Pin state read protection for virtual serial ports
  - Theme application debounced to prevent UI crashes

 -- kryntx <kryntx@users.noreply.github.com>  Sat, 31 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

mouserial (3.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Version 3.0.0 - Complete rewrite in Python/PyQt6
  * Full-featured serial port debugging tool
  - Multiple data display formats (ASCII, HEX, Decimal, Binary)
  - Virtual serial port support (socat-based)
  - Auto-reply functionality
  - Data analysis (Modbus, checksums)
  - Quick command bar
  - Log export with auto-recording and file rotation
  - Dark/Light theme support with font scaling
  - Profile management
  - Pin control (DTR/RTS/CTS/DSR/DCD/RI)

